description:
What: Add sealed sender protocol structs and RPC method constants to core/src/protocol.rs. No functional code — types only.

Algorithm:
1. Read /home/mark/WORK/nie/core/src/protocol.rs to understand existing pattern
2. In rpc_methods module add after existing constants:
   pub const SEALED_BROADCAST: &str = "sealed_broadcast";
   pub const SEALED_DELIVER: &str = "sealed_deliver";
   pub const SEALED_WHISPER: &str = "sealed_whisper";
   pub const SEALED_WHISPER_DELIVER: &str = "sealed_whisper_deliver";
   pub const PUBLISH_HPKE_KEY: &str = "publish_hpke_key";
   pub const GET_HPKE_KEY: &str = "get_hpke_key";
3. Add new param/result structs (after existing BroadcastParams/DeliverParams):
   - SealedBroadcastParams { sealed: Vec<u8> }  // #[serde_as(as="Base64")]
   - SealedDeliverParams { sealed: Vec<u8> }    // #[serde_as(as="Base64")]
   - SealedWhisperParams { to: String, sealed: Vec<u8> }
   - SealedWhisperDeliverParams { to: String, sealed: Vec<u8> }
   - PublishHpkeKeyParams { public_key: Vec<u8> }  // #[serde_as(as="Base64")]
   - GetHpkeKeyParams { pub_id: String }
   - GetHpkeKeyResult { pub_id: String, public_key: Option<Vec<u8>> }  // #[serde_as(as="Option<Base64>")]
4. Follow existing #[serde_as] + #[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)] pattern
5. Run cargo check -p nie-core

Defensive programming rules:
- SealedDeliverParams must NOT have a from field (sealed sender hides origin)
- SealedWhisperDeliverParams: to field is unencrypted (routing); no from field
- All Vec<u8> fields use #[serde_as(as="Base64")] — no raw byte arrays in JSON
- No serde tag issues: these are plain structs, not tagged enums
- Follow exact struct naming from existing codebase (PascalCase, suffix Params/Result)
